description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen to join our busy Emergency department as a Patient Tracker. &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Working alongside a busy team of administrative and clinical staff this is a very valuable and rewarding role.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;em&gt;Essential skills for this role are fast accurate keyboard skills, excellent customer service experience and the ability to communicate effectively at all levels. &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;em&gt;You must be able to multitask, remain calm under pressure, prioritise and troubleshoot within in a busy fast pace environment. Flexibility, reliability, adaptability and working well as part of a team are essential for the Patient Tracker role.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;em&gt;You will be required to provide a variety of administrative tasks all of which improve the patient journey through our department. &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;em&gt;Our administrative team in the Emergency Department has a strong team of staff, all providing a variety of administrative roles including senior secretaries, administrators, team leaders, ward managers assistants and receptionists as well as the patient trackers. &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;em&gt;If you are seeking a challenge and possess the skills required this could be the right job for you. &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;One full time post of 37.5 hrs per week available or two part time posts of 18.75 hrs per week. &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;em&gt;Shifts are: 10.00 - 22.00 hrs covering seven days a week (currently under revision)&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sheena Anderson - Admin Services Lead - sheena.anderson8@nhs.net 01733 673356&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
